<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910305-0116</DOCNO><DOCID>910305-0116.</DOCID><HL>   American Stores Co.,   Albertson's Post Rises   In 4th-Quarter Net</HL><DATE>03/05/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ASC ABS</CO><IN>FOOD RETAILERS AND WHOLESALERS, CONVENIENCE STORES (FDR)EARNINGS (ERN)DIVIDENDS (DIV)BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)</IN><LP>   SAN FRANCISCO -- Two western grocery chains reported arise in profits for their fourth quarter. American Stores Co.of Salt Lake City posted a 62% increase and Albertson's Inc.of Boise, Idaho, posted a 23% rise.   American Stores said net for its fourth quarter ended Feb.2 increased to $86 million, or $2.49 a share, from $53.1million, or $1.61 a share, a year ago. The $2.49 a sharequarterly profit far exceeded even the most bullish analysts,who forecast earnings of as much as $2.16 a share.</LP><TEXT>   Last year's fourth quarter included a $32.5 million chargerelated to the 1985 outbreak of Salmonella, found in milk atits Jewel Cos. unit., offset by a disposition of assets.Sales declined 7% to $5.7 million from $6.1 million a yearago.   American shares surged $4.875 to $75.50 in compositetrading on the New York Stock Exchange.   For the full year, American Stores posted a 54% rise inprofit to $182.4 million, or $5.28 a share, from $118.1million, or $3.45 a share. Revenue was little changed at$22.2 million compared with $22 million. The most recent yearresults were boosted by several factors includingnonrecurring gains, a lower charge related to the last-in,first-out (LIFO) system of inventory accounting, and lowerinterest expenses than the year-ago period, American said.Comparable store sales rose 2.3% for the year and 1.2% forthe quarter.   Albertson's profit rose in line with company expectationsto $73.9 million, or 55 cents a share, in the 13 weeks endedJan. 31, from $60.3 million, or 45 cents a share, in theprior year's period. Sales rose 9% to $2.11 billion from$1.94 billion. The company attributed the gain to a 5% salesincrease in same store sales, and higher gross marginsstemming from increased efficiency of distribution.   For the full year, profit rose 19% to $233.8 million, or$1.75 a share, from $196.6 million, or $1.47 a share. Salesfor the year were were $8.22 billion, up 11% from $7.42billion last year.   The company's stock rose $1 to $39.50 in trading on theBig Board.   Separately, Albertson's said directors authorized adividend increase to 14 cents from 12 cents, payable May 25,to stock of record May 10. Directors also authorized thebuy-back of as many as 6.7 million common shares of stock.   ---   Corrections andamp; Amplifications                                                                                                          AMERICAN STORES Co.'s fourth-quarter sales fell to $5.7billion from $6.1 billion a year earlier. Full-year saleswere $22.2 billion, compared with $22 billion a year earlier.The figures were misstated in yesterday's edition.   (WSJ March 6, 1991)</TEXT></DOC>